descp2: Specifies the reduction to apply to the output: `'none'` | `'mean'` | `'sum'`. `'none'`: no reduction will be applied, `'mean'`: the sum of the output will be divided by the number of elements in the output, `'sum'`: the output will be summed. Note: `size_average` and `reduce` are in the process of being deprecated, and in the meantime, specifying either of those two args will override `reduction`. Default: `'mean'`
